<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>PA&#160;554.  Financial Management in Public Administration.  4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Covers early and current research and theoretical approaches from public finance (primarily state and local), public financial management, and financial governing and policy making that is applicable to the field of public administration. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): Admission to the Public Administration program.<br />
